<br>
Guides are volunteer customer service reps who are the first line of clearing for issues.  They can definitely reject certain requests for help, they can assist with some types of problems (being stuck underground, or dying because of a provable bug in the game), and they gather information necessary for the Admin.  Senior Guides also have the ability to monkey with your surname.<br>
<br>
GM-Admins are paid employees of Sony, and have much greater ability to affect the game, including replacing lost items and setting up guilds.<br>
<br>
A given server will have many Guides, but because they are volunteers there's no telling when any number of them will be available.  A given server will generally have either one GM-Admin, or part of one GM-Admin, depending on what's happening behind the scenes.  Since they are actual employees, Sony is sort of obligated to let them go home now and then, have days off, sleep, etc.<br>
<br>
The petition queue is a first in, first out list.  When you filed your petition, it went onto the bottom of the list.  If it was a slow day and there were lots of Guides, and the GM was on as planned, then your petition would have been quickly answered and completed.  <br>
<br>
However, even when there are several Guides present, three things may prevent you from getting your petition answered:<br>
<br>
1) Current queue length.  If twenty other people have already filed a request for item reimbursement, guild creation, &quot;I WANT TO TAKL TO A GM ABOUT NOT GETTIGN A GODDMAN REZ LAST NITE YOU FUKCS&quot;, and other fascinating problems, then you are #21 on the list.  If the GM-Admin can't 21 problems done before his shift is up... then you don't get it done that day.  Again, the poor guy needs to have a real life too.<br>
<br>
As a suggestion, get your petition in EARLY during the GM's shift if at all possible.  Ask a guide when the GM will be available... sometimes that helps.<br>
<br>
2) The Guides may have been swamped either with a lot of petitions, or with too many nasty time-consuming ones.  There's nothing quite like trying to iron out another stupid Paludal Bandit Camp KS petition to burn a half hour at a time... unless it's listening to guilds bitch about who got to which plane first, and how the other guild (interchangeably) has the worse reputation as a leapfrogger.<br>
<br>
3)  The GM-Admin might simply not have been available.  Sony tells people to petition at so-and-so time, then schedules team meetings for the GMs so they can't work during that time.  *shrug* Must be a big company...<br>
<br>
Anyway, the short answer is, &quot;Keep trying&quot; and eventually it'll happen.  80 percent of the Guides I've known are good people.  Of that crew, 80 percent of THEM are outstandingly good people.  And GM Jindrack... I like him.  He gave my Friskee back an item that she lost by accident once.<br>
<br>
No, I have never worked for Sony.  I am not a Guide.  It's possible that I used to be one, though.<br>
